cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "AGENT-33: Multi-Agent Orchestration Framework with Governance and Evidence Capture"
message: "If you use this software in research, deployment, or derivative work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - name: "AGENT-33 Contributors"
    website: "https://github.com/mattmre/AGENT33-PUBLIC"
repository-code: "https://github.com/mattmre/AGENT33-PUBLIC"
url: "https://github.com/mattmre/AGENT33-PUBLIC"
abstract: >-
  AGENT-33 is a multi-agent orchestration framework that pairs an LLM-agnostic
  agent runtime with a DAG-based workflow engine, a skills and packs ecosystem,
  and a multi-tenant FastAPI control plane. It ships first-class governance
  primitives - tool allowlists, autonomy budgets, two-layer review automation,
  and signed release artifacts - alongside an evidence capture layer that
  records traces, outcomes, and lineage for every agent invocation. The runtime
  is provider-agnostic across Ollama, OpenAI-compatible APIs, and MCP servers;
  memory is backed by pgvector plus a BM25 hybrid retriever; and operational
  surfaces include code execution sandboxes, evaluation gates, knowledge
  ingestion crons, and release-automation rollback. The platform is designed
  for self-hosted, air-gap-capable deployment with per-tenant isolation.
